y\cos\alpha.$$Because $x\ne y$, this yields $$\cos\alpha={{x^2-y^2}\over{2\cdot180(x-y)}} ={{x+y}\over360} =
{280\over360}=\boxed{\frac{7}{9}}.$$[asy]
